# Stock Market Performance

Apple's stock price reflected the strong operational results throughout the fiscal year. The following section visualizes the daily closing price for the trailing 12 months leading up to the earnings announcement.

```mdcc_chart caption="AAPL Daily Closing Price (Last 12 Months)" label="fig:historical-price"
# Load data from stable financial endpoint (Stooq) as a mirror of Yahoo-style data
# This is used to ensure reliable network fetch without complex browser headers
url = "https://stooq.com/q/d/l/?s=aapl.us&f=sdxcvl&i=d"
prices = pd.read_csv(url)

# Convert Date and Filter for 2025
prices['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(prices['Date'])
df_2025 = prices[(prices['Date'] >= '2025-01-01') & (prices['Date'] <= '2025-12-27')]

# Create Chart
alt.Chart(df_2025).mark_line(color="#0071E3", strokeWidth=2).encode(
    x=alt.X('Date:T', title='Date'),
    y=alt.Y('Close:Q', title='Closing Price ($)', scale=alt.Scale(zero=False)),
    tooltip=['Date', 'Close']
).properties(
    width=640,
    height=320
).configure_view(
    stroke=None
)
```

As seen in @fig:historical-price, the stock price demonstrated steady upward momentum during 2025, buoyed by anticipation of the AI-integrated product lineup.

```mdcc_table caption="Recent Stock Price Performance Summary" label="tbl:stock-stats"
url = "https://stooq.com/q/d/l/?s=aapl.us&f=sdxcvl&i=d"
prices = pd.read_csv(url)
prices['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(prices['Date'])
df_2025 = prices[(prices['Date'] >= '2025-01-01') & (prices['Date'] <= '2025-12-27')]

stats = {
    "Period": ["Start 2025", "End Q1 2026 (Dec 27)", "Year High", "Year Low"],
    "Price ($)": [
        df_2025['Close'].iloc[0],
        df_2025['Close'].iloc[-1],
        df_2025['Close'].max(),
        df_2025['Close'].min()
    ]
}
pd.DataFrame(stats)
```

---

# Quarterly Segment Analysis

### iPhone: The Power of AI and Design
The iPhone 17 family set all-time records for any quarter, growing 23% year-over-year. The integration of advanced AI capabilities ("Apple Intelligence 2.0") acted as a major catalyst for the "Supercycle" analysts had predicted.

### Services: Consistent High-Margin Growth
Services revenue reached an all-time record of $30 billion. Growth was broad-based across App Store, Apple Music, and iCloud, with advertising and payment services reaching new peaks.

### Regional Outlook
Geographically, Apple set revenue records in all major regions:
*   **Americas**: Strong 14% growth driven by US consumer spending.
*   **Greater China**: Rebounded with 11% growth after a period of volatility.
*   **Europe & Japan**: Set all-time records supported by favorable currency dynamics.
*   **Emerging Markets**: India and Southeast Asia continue to be high-growth priorities.

---

# Conclusion

Apple's Q1 2026 results demonstrate the resilience of its hardware-software-services ecosystem. The record revenue and earnings, combined with an expanding installed base of 2.5 billion devices, positions the company strongly for the remainder of the fiscal year. 

Future growth is expected to be sustained by continued Services momentum and the expansion of spatial computing and AI-integrated hardware across the lineup.
